        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-07T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-07T12:00:00-05:00" n="272" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Bulgaria)/8–745:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-07T19:00:00+02:00">August 7, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 7—4:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>428. Day after issuance Potsdam declaration local newspaper <hi rend="italic">Izgrev</hi> published article containing among other things suggestion that
                    ACC was about to become really tripartite. Biryusov has just had editor in to
                    tell him that such “stupid and unpatriotic” interpretations will not be
                    tolerated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Barnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
